    "content": "nullManage Your Quotes with CPQ\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Manage Your Quotes with CPQ\n Salesforce CPQ Patch Notes\n Getting Started with Salesforce CPQ\n CPQ Products\n Create and Edit CPQ Quotes\n Send Your CPQ Quotes\n Advanced Approvals\n Manage Your CPQ Orders\n Manage Your Subscriptions and Assets\n Amend Your Contracts and Assets\n CPQ Amendment Fields and Settings\n Amend Your Contracts\n Amend a Contract from an Opportunity\n Guidelines for Amending from a Contract with Multiple Subscription...\n Guidelines for Amending Subscription Start Dates\n Amend Your Assets\n Create an Add-On Opportunity\n Amendment Processes\n Amending MDQ Products\n Terminating Subscriptions\n Asset Upgrades\n Guidelines for Amending Contracts\n Renew Your Contracts and Assets\n Printable Tip Sheets & User Guides — For Salesforce CPQ\n Explore CPQ Solution Kits\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE CPQ\nAmendment Processes\n\nSalesforce CPQ offers several ways to manage the subscriptions and assets you’re amending.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: All Salesforce CPQ Editions\nAmending MDQ Products\nAmend a contract containing multidimensional quoting (MDQ) products. This process is useful if you want to change a multiple-year contract partway through its term.\nTerminating Subscriptions\nRemove a subscription when making an amendment.\nAsset Upgrades\nThe asset upgrade and downgrade features let your sales reps replace an asset with a different asset from within the quote line editor. This feature is useful for processing upgrades.\nGuidelines for Amending Contracts\nWhen you’re ready to amend a contract, review our guidelines.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
